headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 23 points and Dennis Schroder had six points in the final 76 seconds as the Boston Celtics beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 98-92 on Monday night, splitting their two-game set at Rocket Mortgage FieldHouse.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 23, Celtics beat Cavaliers 98-92 to split set

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 22 points and Tyrese Haliburton added 17 points and 10 assists as the Sacramento Kings routed the Detroit Pistons 129-107 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield, Haliburton lead Kings, rout Pistons, end 4-game skid

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Moments after being serenaded with chants of “M-V-P! M-V-P!” at the free throw line, fan favorite Montrezl Harrell drew a foul on the other end of the court and pounded his chest as the home crowd roared in approval.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards stay hot, erase 19-point deficit to beat Pelicans

headlines.description: — Trae Young and John Collins each scored 23 points and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Orlando Magic 129-111 on Monday night for their second straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Collins each score 23 as Hawks beat Magic 129-111

events.name: Indiana Pacers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The New York Knicks were clearly not going to shoot their way out of their slump.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks limit Pacers to 2 baskets in 4th quarter, win 92-84

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had 29 points and 11 rebounds, Tim Hardaway Jr. scored 13 of his 19 in the fourth quarter and the Dallas Mavericks rallied behind a small-ball lineup to beat the Denver Nuggets 111-101 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Small lineup helps Mavs rally in 4th to beat Nuggets 111-101

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 22 points, six rebounds and six assists, Jaren Jackson Jr. added 18 points and the Memphis Grizzlies beat Houston 136-102 Monday night, sending the Rockets to their 12th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies send Houston to its 12 straight defeat 136-102

headlines.description: — Chris Paul scored 19 of his 21 points in the fourth quarter, Devin Booker had 29 and the Phoenix Suns beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 99-96 Monday night for their ninth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul gets 19 in 4th, Suns beat Timberwolves, 9th win in row

events.name: Miami Heat at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 26 points and the short-handed Miami Heat beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 103-90 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro scores 26, short-handed Heat top Thunder 103-90

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — If only the Trail Blazers could figure out why they're successful at home but struggle on the road.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum scores 29 as Trail Blazers beat Raptors 118-113

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored a season-high 38 points and Zach LaVine had added 26 in the Chicago Bulls' 121-103 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, LaVine lead Bulls' 121-103 rout of LA; Davis tossed
